<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - CONTROL
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>CONTROL ASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure key switch is off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the operator side half of the instrument panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the screws that fasten the control assembly to the instrument panel. Pull the
                    control assembly away from the instrument panel. Disconnect the A/C push button and fan electrical
                    connectors (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601416" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601416" filename="../figg16/G1601416.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Control Assembly and Cables</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. A/C SWITCH</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BLOWER SWITCH</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. TEMPERATURE CONTROL</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. AIR OUTLET SELECTOR</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift to unsnap the control cables from the two rack and pinion assemblies. Disconnect
                    the "Z" bent cable ends from the two racks (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the control assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1 id="hl1601405">
                <para count="1">Connect the control cables to the control assembly rack and pinions as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">The cable with the white mounting tab to the Air Outlet Selector knob.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">The cable with the red mounting tab (heater-only unit) or a black mounting tab
                        (Blend-Air unit) to the Temperature Control knob (Item 3,
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1601416">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the wiring harness connectors to the blower and A/C switches.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the control assembly in the instrument panel and fasten with two screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the instrument panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the operation and adjustment of the cables. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16014_HL1601403.xml" xrefid="hl1601403">MAINTENANCE</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
